  "active_lock_reason": "resolved",
  "body": "When estimating gas automatically, Buidler [multiplies an estimation provided by a remote node by a configurable multiplier](https://github.com/nomiclabs/buidler/blob/master/src/internal/core/providers/gas-providers.ts#L54). This multiplication could result in a number higher than the block gas limit, preventing the transaction to execute, when it would probably be executable.\r\n\r\nTo fix this, we should get a block (a single one is fine) to have an upper bound for gas estimation's. If this bound is surpassed, we should just use it (or a slightly lower number).\r\n\r\n",
